Consider the regex matcher instead:


```
List<String> questions = new ArrayList<>();
String newLineRegex = "(\r\n|\r|\n){2}"; // 2 new lines
Matcher m = Pattern.compile(newLineRegex).matcher(fileContents);
int prev = 0;
while (m.find()) {
    String question= input.substring(prev, m.end());
    prev = m.end();
    questions.add(question);
}
questions.add(input.substring(prev)); // capture trailing text
return questions.asArray();
```

or:
`fileContents = fileContents.replace("\r\n", "\n").replace("\r", "\n");`
before you split by `\n\n` would also work.

